-- UBS’s Carsten Kengeter to Leave as Sam Molinaro Assumes Duties
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   H a r p e r
-- 2013-02-12T19:43:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-12/ubs-s-carsten-kengeter-to-leave-as-sam-molinaro-assumes-duties.html
UBS AG’s Carsten Kengeter, the
former investment bank chief picked to wind down the non-core
asset portfolio, is leaving the firm.  He will be succeeded by Sam Molinaro, the company wrote
today in an internal memo to employees. Karina Byrne, a company
spokeswoman in New York, confirmed the memo’s contents. The
Financial Times reported the change earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Harper in New York at 
